==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imbathe
<hw>Im*bathe"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> in + <ets>bathe</ets>. Cf. <er>Embathe</er>.]</ety>
<def>To bathe; to wash freely; to immerse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And gave her to his daughters to <qex>imbathe</qex>⟦br⟧
In nectared lavers strewed with asphodel.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imbay</ent>⟦br⟧
